    "causal_summary": "The J1 to J4 generator phases harden how the spec-kit writes `description.json` and `graph-metadata.json`, but they ship their new behavior behind default-OFF flags so the on-disk repo is untouched. Phase 033 lands the identity-resolver merge safety, phase 034 lands the scoped backfill boundary, phase 035 lands the idempotent content-hashed description writes and the targeted cache upsert, and phase 036 lands the generated-metadata validator that enforces the enum-clean `derived.status`, the `.opencode/specs/` path prefix and the preserved `parent_id` and `children_ids`. With every one of those flags OFF, the existing generated JSON across the repo still carries the legacy format the new contract rejects, wall-clock churn, prose statuses, unprefixed paths and dropped parent links.",
